item.title: Myrlie Evers-Williams - Medgar Evers, NAACP & 'For Us, The Living'
item.description: (1933-) Who Is Myrlie Evers-Williams? Born in 1933, Myrlie Evers-Williams was the wife of murdered civil rights activist Medgar Evers. While fighting to bring his killer to justice, Evers-Williams also continued her husband's work with her book, For Us, The Living. She also wrote Watch Me Fly: What I Learned on the Way to Becoming the Woman I Was Meant to Be. Evers-Williams served as chair of the NAACP from 1995 to 1998.
